author: knoxnews.com
title: Where are they now? Cole West - PrepXtra
text:
Cole West
East Tennessee State, football
Oneida High School
Now: West, a 6-foot-2, 198-pound strong safety, ranks sixth with 18 tackles for the Buccaneers, who resumed football competition this season after a 12-year hiatus. The redshirt freshman opened his college career with a team-high 9 1/2 tackles in ETSU's season-opening loss to Kennesaw State. He finished with four stops for ETSU (0-5) in last week's loss to Saint Francis (Pa.).
Then: West was a two-sport star in high school, scoring more than 2,000 points in basketball and earning all-state honors as a defensive back in football. He rushed for 927 yards and nine touchdowns on 130 carries as a senior in 2013, and finished with 56 tackles, five interceptions and a fumble recovery. He participated in Tennessee East vs. West All-Star Game.
Chris Thomas
